The grooming services here are not good. Each groomer is different and depending on their knowledge, they may or may not give your dog the correct cut for their breed. We have a West Highland Terrier who is rarely groomed properly.   We used to overlook the grooming issue up until recently. We asked the groomer to give our dog a shorter cut for the summer, as in the same style but just shorter in length. When we got him back the groomer had completely shaved off all of the dog's fur, basically leaving him with a buzz cut. Also, they must have cut him because there is a spot that keeps reopening, bleeding, and matting his fur. It has yet to heal and it has been over a month now since his appointment. We are taking him to the vet and he may have to have surgery in order to correct this mistake.

