As someone who used to work in retail (not at Nordstrom but one of their competitors), I will say that this is an excellent company. People complain in their reviews that the employees are concerned about making their commission-well obviously! That's how they make most of their money. Pretty much all retail companies use a commission structure for paying their employees. If you want better service you need to stick to one  sales associate to show that you are a serious buyer and not wasting their time.   Nordstrom has the best quality, brands, and pricing of products. It's hard to find good quality items at a decent price anymore but Nordstrom has them. Free shipping, easy returns, price matching, and ordering for you in store are some of the best perks that Nordstrom offers.

